{"ts":"2026-06-27T00:33:20.858Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Detailing API Security**\n\nI'm now detailing security requirements, focusing on HTTPS-only access and rate limits for authentication and sandbox endpoints. CORS headers will restrict access to the domain. I'm also planning JWT bearer authentication for authenticated queries.\n\nI'm developing a mock/abstracted OTP service class for flexibility, allowing integration with services like Mailgun, SendGrid, or AWS SES later on.\nI've begun documenting each of the 11 API endpoints in detail, starting with `POST /api/blueprint/generate`. I'm outlining its purpose, security considerations (OTP or JWT), and payload/response schemas using Pydantic/JSON. I'm focusing on completeness, including fields like `industry`, `compliance_regime`, etc., with data types and restrictions.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
