{"ts":"2026-06-27T00:36:43.313Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"m2um7quq","input":{"summary":"Created the comprehensive API contract documentation file 'docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md' to guide the future transition from Phase 3 (frontend-only simulations) to a high-performance Python FastAPI backend (Phase 4).\n\nThe document covers:\n1. Executive Architecture Overview: Outlines Next.js client-side and FastAPI server-side data exchange with detailed topology diagrams.\n2. Phase 3 Interactive Tools Status: Details local storage retention and simulation boundaries for tools like Blueprint Builder, Readiness Assessment, ROI Calculator, RFP/Proposal Builder, Client Sandbox, Foundry Studio DAG workflow canvas, and Agent Marketplace.\n3. Phase 4 Target Backend System Architecture: Specifications for FastAPI, PostgreSQL relational database, Redis cache, S3-compatible Object Storage, and Passwordless OTP authentication via business email.\n4. FastAPI API Endpoint Catalog: Complete HTTP request/response schemas, security requirements, and illustrative response examples for the following 11 endpoints:\n   - POST /api/blueprint/generate\n   - POST /api/assessment/score\n   - POST /api/roi/calculate\n   - POST /api/contact/submit\n   - POST /api/proposal/generate\n   - POST /api/auth/request-otp\n   - POST /api/auth/verify-otp\n   - POST /api/newsletter/subscribe\n   - POST /api/sandbox/run\n   - POST /api/foundry/workflow\n   - GET /api/marketplace/agents\n5. Security & Environment Configuration: A premium '.env.example' environment template mapping core networking, PostgreSQL, Redis, SMTP/OTP, AWS S3 buckets, and sandbox constraints.\n6. Local State Synchronization Strategy: Migration guidance outlining state hydration, optimistic client-side UI computations, background sync debouncing, and graceful local simulation fallback triggers.\n\nRan a clean production build check ('npm run build') to verify repository compilation and validate that no warnings or runtime dependencies were affected. All systems are verified and build fully succeeds.","verified":true}}}
